---
source: crates/duckpond/tests/parse_spec.rs
expression: spec
---
SPEC: Authentication
  SUMMARY: Allows users to sign in with email and password. Primary auth
    mechanism for consumer accounts.
  DESCRIPTION:
    This capability is the foundation for all user-facing access
      control. It covers the happy path (credentials accepted) and the
      most common failure modes (credentials rejected, account locked).
      Delegated auth via third-party providers is a separate capability
      under `auth/oauth/`.
  REQUIREMENT: Email-password login
    The system SHALL allow a registered user to authenticate.
    MARKS: test: code
    SCENARIO: Valid credentials
      WHENS:
        the user submits correct credentials
      THENS:
        the system issues a session token
